<p>
You do not always need to choose the day, month, and year at which to
start and end the search.  For example, if you choose a start date of
"June" and an end date of "August," messages posted between June 1 and
August 31 of this year will be searched.
</p>
<p>
If you choose a start date but no end date, messages posted during 
the time frame of the start date will be searched.  For example,
if you choose a start date of March 2003, messages between March 1
and March 31, 2003, will be searched.
</p>
<p>
The author and subject search patterns are optional.  If you do
not use a pattern, all of the messages in the time frame you chose
will be shown or mailed.  See the
$HELP:PATTERNS
help document to learn more about search patterns.
</p>


